In my [previous post](https://vincentp.me/blog/optimising-my-jekyll-workflow) I discussed streamlining some of my proceses and optimising my code.

A month after publishing that post I needed to update my version of Node from an old version 4.5.0 that was needed for a client, to the latest 7.7.3 version. This unfortunately caused Pleeease to stop functioning.

I [raised a bug ](https://github.com/iamvdo/pleeease/issues/82#issuecomment-287345139) with the author
